track_notes: This is a tough hike in part due to poor footing for most of the 8 mile RT hike but also because it is relentlessly uphill. We generally take 2 liters of water. As you get closer to the mountain (about an hour in), you will begin a left turn switchback. There will be 24 more to follow counting each left turn as an odd number and each right turn as even. The reward is a beautiful, park-like summit with fantastic views. Our 2017 hike was under a 2 hour ascent.
track_title: Hermit Peak, one of NMs iconic mountains

track_notes: There was recent re-routing of the lower part of the trail so this new track was made.
